README

last updated: 06-Apr-2011

Installation
============
sudo gem1.9.1 install optparse-simple

Examples
========
Here's a quick start example:

require 'optparse-simple'

options =<<EOF
dxxx -d --dxxx n/a false 
idxxx n/a n/a \\w+ false
EOF

ops = OptParseSimple.new(options).parse %w(-d 4)
#=> {:dxxx=>nil, :idxxx=>"4"} 


Another quick example:

require 'optparse-simple'

options =<<OPTIONS
username -u --username \\w+ true
  invalid username
  you must enter a username
password -p --pasword \\w+ true
  invalid password
  you must enter a password
keyword n/a n/a [\\w\+]+ true
  invalid keyword
  you must enter a keyword e.g. --keyword=ruby
OPTIONS

args = %w(-u james -p secret fun)
OptParseSimple.new(options).parse %w(-u james -p secret fun)
#=> {:username=>"james", :password=>"secret", :keyword=>"fun"}